  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you remember, we were all surprised to see that he came to the point of saying in his final statement-- he didn't say all of this during his-- while he was on the witness stand.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in his final statement, [CLEARS THROAT] he said, I have been guilty of indoctrinating German youth in-- into the hands of a barbarian, whom I did not recognize as a barbarian at the time.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, you know that's-- from the prosecution's point of view and from history's point of view, that's quite a statement to have come from the former [CLEARS THROAT] Hitler Youth leader and gauleiter of Vienna.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The final statements, which is when I think he said it, were not under oath.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's, incidentally, legally speaking, from the point of view of jurisprudence, an addition that was present in the Nuremberg trial, which does not exist in Anglo-Saxon practice, in American practice, or British practice.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At the end of a trial, a defendant is allowed to speak, just before the tribunal goes into recess to consider its judgement.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he's not to be questioned by anybody.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He makes any statement he wants.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is a part of normal legal practice in the continent of Europe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he-- his defense basically was that I didn't really think that Hitler was aiming at any kind of war, and that I was greatly impressed by the injustices, which was done-- had been done to Germany at the end of World War I, the Treaty of Versailles, and things like that.",
      "word_count": 52
    }
  ],
